data.title: Make A Gift | Centre College
data.snippet:
Give to Scholarships

## Experiential Learning

A Centre education empowers students to be global change-makers. Courses take place inside and outside of the classroom, on and off campus—even abroad, and allow students to get credit for hands-on learning with options like internships, community-based learning, faculty-mentored research, and active participation in the arts. Donor support is essential to fulfilling this promise.

Give to Experiential Learning

## Campus & Community

Annual gifts that support community-building areas—such as diversity, environmental initiatives, the arts, and campus organizations—ensure Centre remains a welcoming home for all students.

Give to the Centre Community

## Centre Fund

Gifts to the Centre Fund provide vital flexibility, allowing the College to address student and institutional needs as they arise. Comprising about three-fourths of annual gifts, these contributions bridge the gap between the cost of tuition and the true expense of delivering the Centre Experience.

Give to the Centre Fund

## Scholarships

Ninety percent of Centre students receive financial aid, making the Centre Experience accessible to all. Unrestricted gifts and strong support for scholarships are essential to maintaining affordability and providing opportunities for students of all backgrounds.

Give to Scholarships

data.snippet:
### The Bonner Program

Supported by the Office of Civic and Community Engagement, the good work of Bonner Scholars and Bonner Leaders at Centre impacts the community through direct service at local nonprofits.

Bonner Program

#### Community Engagement Programs

The mission of Centre College is to prepare students for lives of learning, leadership, and service in a global society. Centre offers a wide-variety of programs and ways to get involved.

Community Engagement

# Civic and Community Engagement

 Administrative Office

Calling all changemakers: the world is waiting for you!

The Office of Civic and Community Engagement provides opportunities for Centre students, faculty and staff to engage with local communities through service and civic action. Find a future career in nonprofits or community organizing—or just get started today on making the world a better place. Make service a part of your Centre Experience!
